  <a href="#0" id="0">
   In this paper we proposed a novel alternative to topic labelling which do not rely on external data sources.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   To the best of out knowledge no existing work has been formally studied for automatic labelling through summarisation.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   This experiment shows that existing summarisation techniques can be exploited to provide a better label of a topic, extending in this way a topic s information by providing a richer context than top-terms.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   These results show that there is room to further improve upon existing summarisation techniques to cater for generating candidate labels.
  </a>
